@startuml bat_bms_to_cpc_charge_port_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title BAT_BMS To CPC Charge-Port Signal Flow\n(BMS pack state + OBC + vehicle state -> CPC charge-port publication)

participant "BAT_BMS\npack-state producer" as BMS #E8F7E8
participant "OBC\ncharge-source state" as OBC #E8F0FE
participant "Vehicle state\nDriveState" as Veh #F4F7FB
participant "CPC\ncharge-port owner" as CPC #FFF4CC
participant "Charge observers /\ncomfort outputs" as Obs #FCE8FF

== Charge-Port Inputs ==

BMS -> CPC : frmBatBmsStateMsg\nBmsState / PackSoc / PackTemp
OBC -> CPC : frmOnBoardChargerStateMsg\nOBC / plug state
Veh -> CPC : frmVehicleStateCanMsg\nDriveState
activate CPC
CPC -> CPC : normalize stale BMS / OBC / vehicle inputs
CPC -> CPC : derive PortLockState / PlugState
CPC -> CPC : derive ChargeEnable / ThermalState
CPC -> CPC : derive ChargeTargetSoc
note right of CPC
Representative inputs
- BmsState
- PackSoc
- PackTemp
- OBC state
- DriveState

Representative outputs
- PortLockState
- PlugState
- ChargeEnable
- ThermalState
- ChargeTargetSoc
end note

== Charge-Port Publish ==

CPC -> Obs : frmChargePortStateMsg
CPC -> Obs : traceable charge-port / thermal state
deactivate CPC

note over BMS, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. BAT_BMS publishes pack state and thermal context
2. CPC combines BMS, OBC, and vehicle drive state
3. CPC derives charge-port lock/enable/thermal outputs
4. Charge observers and tests verify charging readiness
end note

@enduml
